	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64422524">We keep reading about high pressure on the nation's grid, its security issues, etc., and have for some time. So it would be good to know how much of this upgrade is really stuff that should be (should have been?) done by now regardless, and how much is specifically in support of EVs. Many reports I've read suggest that just dealing with the non-EV part would likely require major grid changes, if not wholesale replacement over time.</div>
	</div>

